00:00:06.850 --> 00:00:09.340
Internet

00:00:09.340 --> 00:00:10.570
On the Wii U Menu,

00:00:10.570 --> 00:00:11.570
select System Settings,

00:00:11.570 --> 00:00:12.570
then Internet.

00:00:12.570 --> 00:00:17.080
Connect to the internet,

00:00:17.080 --> 00:00:18.370
and your Wii U will search for networks.

00:00:18.370 --> 00:00:21.650
select your network,

00:00:21.650 --> 00:00:23.850
Enter the security key if necessary,

00:00:23.850 --> 00:00:26.410
and your Wii U will check the connection.

00:00:26.410 --> 00:00:31.750
Once connected, you will be asked to check
for System Updates.

00:00:31.750 --> 00:00:32.820
System Update

00:00:32.820 --> 00:00:34.750
You can update the system now

00:00:34.750 --> 00:00:37.820
or press cancel while connected to the Internet

00:00:37.820 --> 00:00:42.940
to download the update in the background.

00:00:42.940 --> 00:00:47.899
From experience, the update can take up to
over an hour to download,

00:00:47.899 --> 00:00:55.319
while using over six hundred megabytes of
internet usage.

00:00:55.319 --> 00:00:56.729
If you decided to press cancel

00:00:56.729 --> 00:00:58.559
and put the update in the background.

00:00:58.559 --> 00:01:01.819
A notification will come up to tell you

00:01:01.819 --> 00:01:09.170
of the System Update's successful download.

00:01:09.170 --> 00:01:15.240
Updating will take approximately over ten
minutes.

00:01:15.240 --> 00:01:17.229
If you are not using a Wi-Fi network,

00:01:17.229 --> 00:01:19.680
in the Internet Settings you can select Connection
Types

00:01:19.680 --> 00:01:22.480
for other methods of connecting to the Internet.

00:01:22.480 --> 00:01:25.850
You can also check you current Internet Connections.

00:01:25.850 --> 00:01:33.240
Here you can Change Settings, Delete Settings
or perform a Connection Test.

00:01:33.240 --> 00:01:37.000
In Internet Settings you can also Find Recommended
Connection Type,

00:01:37.000 --> 00:01:41.070
where it will lead you through a setup process.

